Problem Statement:
Design the core Low-Level system for a Ride-Sharing service (like Uber).
Core Requirements:
Rider: Can request a ride from a source to a destination. Can see the estimated fare before booking.
Driver: Can go online/offline. Can accept or reject a ride request. Can update the ride status (In-progress, Completed).
Ride Matching: The system should match a rider with an available driver based on specific criteria (e.g., nearest driver).
Pricing: The fare should be calculated based on the distance. The system must support dynamic pricing (Surge pricing during peak hours, Standard pricing otherwise).

Ride:
id, source, destination, User driver, user rider, estimatedFare, enum RideStatus

enum RideStatus:
REQUESTED
ACCEPTED
IN_PROGRESS
COMPLETED
CANCELLED

PricingStrategy: interface
calculatePrice

NormalPricing: class

